        <p>&#160;</p>
        <table style="border-left-style: Solid;border-top-style: Solid;border-right-style: Solid;border-bottom-style: Solid;border-left-width: 2px;border-right-width: 2px;border-top-width: 2px;border-bottom-width: 2px;border-left-color: #5f5f5f;border-right-color: #5f5f5f;border-top-color: #5f5f5f;border-bottom-color: #5f5f5f;width: 100%;border-spacing: 0px;border-spacing: 0px;" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
            <col style="width: 15.979%;" />
            <col style="width: 84.021%;" />
            <tr valign="top">
                <td colspan="1" rowspan="1" style="width: 15.979%;padding-right: 10px;padding-left: 10px;background-color: #c9c9c9;border-left-width: 3px;border-left-style: Solid;border-left-color: #ffffff;border-right-width: 3px;border-right-style: Solid;border-right-color: #ffffff;border-bottom-width: 3px;border-bottom-color: #ffffff;border-bottom-style: Solid;border-top-width: 3px;border-top-style: Solid;border-top-color: #ffffff;" bgcolor="#C9C9C9" width="15.979%">
                    <p style="font-weight: bold;">Purpose</p>
                </td>
                <td colspan="1" rowspan="1" style="width: 84.021%;padding-right: 10px;padding-left: 10px;background-color: #eaeaea;border-right-width: 3px;border-right-style: Solid;border-right-color: #ffffff;border-bottom-width: 3px;border-bottom-color: #ffffff;border-bottom-style: Solid;border-top-width: 3px;border-top-color: #ffffff;border-top-style: Solid;" bgcolor="#EAEAEA" width="84.021%">
                    <p data-mc-conditions="Primary.Locale">Disables guardianPRO for a certain period of time (i.e.: system maintenance time band).</p>
                    <p style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #000000;">Enables/disables notifications to listed contacts.  </span>
                    </p>
                    <p style="color: #000000;">Indicates guardianPRO notification recipients.</p>
                    <p data-mc-conditions="Primary.Locale"><span data-mc-conditions="Primary.Locale">(optional) Setup active alarm controls and variable checks.</span>
                    </p>
                </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top">
                <td colspan="1" rowspan="1" style="width: 15.979%;padding-right: 10px;padding-left: 10px;background-color: #c9c9c9;border-left-color: #ffffff;border-left-style: Solid;border-left-width: 3px;border-right-color: #ffffff;border-right-style: Solid;border-right-width: 3px;border-bottom-style: Solid;border-bottom-color: #ffffff;border-bottom-width: 3px;" bgcolor="#C9C9C9" width="15.979%">
                    <p style="font-weight: bold;">Description</p>
                </td>
                <td colspan="1" rowspan="1" style="width: 84.021%;padding-right: 10px;padding-left: 10px;background-color: #eaeaea;border-right-color: #ffffff;border-right-style: Solid;border-right-width: 3px;border-bottom-style: Solid;border-bottom-color: #ffffff;border-bottom-width: 3px;" bgcolor="#EAEAEA" width="84.021%">
                    <p style="color: #000000;">Refer to chapter <a href="guardianPRO__concetti_di_base.htm">guardianPRO: basic concepts</a>, to see why active alarm control and variable checks are beneficial.</p>
                </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top">
                <td colspan="1" rowspan="1" style="width: 15.979%;padding-right: 10px;padding-left: 10px;background-color: #c9c9c9;border-left-width: 3px;border-left-style: Solid;border-left-color: #ffffff;border-right-width: 3px;border-right-style: Solid;border-right-color: #ffffff;border-bottom-width: 3px;border-bottom-color: #ffffff;border-bottom-style: Solid;" bgcolor="#C9C9C9" width="15.979%">
                    <p style="font-weight: bold;">What to do first</p>
                </td>
                <td colspan="1" rowspan="1" style="width: 84.021%;padding-right: 10px;padding-left: 10px;background-color: #eaeaea;border-right-width: 3px;border-right-style: Solid;border-right-color: #ffffff;border-bottom-width: 3px;border-bottom-color: #ffffff;border-bottom-style: Solid;" bgcolor="#EAEAEA" width="84.021%">
                    <p style="color: #000000;">Set the maximum alarm management time.</p>
                    <p style="color: #000000;"><span style="color: #000000;">Set up the notification channels to be used.</span>
                    </p>
                </td>
            </tr>
        </table>
        <p>&#160;</p>
        <table style="width: 100%;border-left-color: #000000;border-left-width: 1px;border-right-color: #000000;border-right-width: 1px;background-color: #c0c0c0;border-spacing: 0px;border-spacing: 0px;" cellspacing="0" bgcolor="#C0C0C0" width="100%">
            <col style="width: 6.855%;" />
            <col style="width: 93.145%;" />
            <tr valign="top">
                <td colspan="1" rowspan="1" style="width: 6.855%;padding-right: 10px;padding-left: 10px;background-color: #cccccc;border-bottom-style: Solid;border-bottom-color: #ffffff;border-bottom-width: 2px;" bgcolor="#CCCCCC" valign="middle" width="6.855%">
                    <p class="Note">
                        <img src="../Resources/Images/AAwarning.gif" style="border: none;width: 32px;height: 32px;float: none;border-style: none;border-style: none;" width="32" height="32" border="0" />
                    </p>
                </td>
                <td colspan="1" rowspan="1" style="width: 93.145%;padding-right: 1px;padding-left: 1px;background-color: #cccccc;border-bottom-width: 2px;border-bottom-color: #ffffff;border-bottom-style: Solid;" bgcolor="#CCCCCC" width="93.145%">
                    <p>guardianPRO notifications warns the user of malfunctions and faults that jeopardize entire system operations. If notifications are disabled, guardianPRO will continue its control activity but can only run events or reboot the system where applicable.</p>
                </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top">
                <td colspan="1" rowspan="1" style="width: 6.855%;padding-right: 10px;padding-left: 10px;background-color: #cccccc;border-bottom-width: 2px;border-bottom-color: #ffffff;border-bottom-style: Solid;" bgcolor="#CCCCCC" valign="middle" width="6.855%">
                    <p class="Note">
                        <img src="../Resources/Images/AAinfo.gif" style="border: none;width: 32px;height: 32px;float: none;border-style: none;border-style: none;" width="32" height="32" border="0" />
                    </p>
                </td>
                <td colspan="1" rowspan="1" style="width: 93.145%;padding-right: 1px;padding-left: 1px;background-color: #cccccc;border-bottom-style: Solid;border-bottom-color: #ffffff;border-bottom-width: 2px;" bgcolor="#CCCCCC" width="93.145%">
                    <p>In general, system status controls are always on even if guardianPRO is disabled for several days. Temporarily disabling guardianPRO effects guardianPRO notifications following negative results: check results are saved in the guardianPRO log but new events, notifications or reboots are not run.</p>
                </td>
            </tr>
        </table>
        <p class="TitoloInterno">
            <img src="../Resources/Images/AAaction.gif" style="border: none;float: none;width: 32px;height: 32px;border-style: none;border-style: none;" width="32" height="32" border="0" /> Action</p>
        <div class="MCDropDown MCDropDown_Open dropDown"><span class="MCDropDownHead dropDownHead"><a href="javascript:void(0);" class="MCDropDownHotSpot dropDownHotspot MCDropDownHotSpot_">Selecting guardianPRO notification recipients
                                                                       </a></span>
            <div class="MCDropDownBody dropDownBody">
                <div>
                    <ul style="list-style: disc;" type="disc">
                        <li class="p" value="1">
                            <p>Click Enable notifications.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="p" value="2">
                            <p>Select an addressee from the address book</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="p" value="3">
                            <p>Click <img src="../Resources/Images/dbllistbox/arrowdx_on.png" style="border: none;float: none;width: 54px;height: 19px;border-style: none;border-style: none;" width="54" height="19" border="0" /> to include it in the list of guardianPRO recipients</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="p" value="4">
                            <p>Repeat for other addressees</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="MCDropDown MCDropDown_Open dropDown"><span class="MCDropDownHead dropDownHead"><a href="javascript:void(0);" class="MCDropDownHotSpot dropDownHotspot MCDropDownHotSpot_">(optional) Selecting variables whose variations are controlled
                                                                        
                       </a></span>
            <div class="MCDropDownBody dropDownBody">
                <div>
                    <ul style="list-style: disc;" type="disc">
                        <li class="p" value="1">
                            <p>Click <span style="font-weight: bold;">Check probe variation</span> to be warned when, for a certain amount of time, the indicated variables always read the same value.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="p" value="2">
                            <p>Selecting a device</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="p" value="3">
                            <p>Selecting a variable</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="p" value="4">
                            <p>Click <img src="../Resources/Images/dbllistbox/arrowdx_on.png" style="border: none;float: none;width: 54px;height: 19px;border-style: none;border-style: none;" width="54" height="19" border="0" /> to include it in the list of monitored variables.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="p" value="5">
                            <p>Repeat for other variables</p>
                        </li>
                        <li class="p" value="6">
                            <p style="font-weight: normal;">Indicate the <span style="font-weight: bold;">Number of consecutive constant values to signal an error.</span></p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <p class="TitoloInterno">
            <img src="../Resources/Images/AAaction.gif" style="border: none;float: none;width: 32px;height: 32px;border-style: none;border-style: none;" width="32" height="32" border="0" /> Other actions</p>
        <p>Common used buttons</p>
        <table style="border-left-style: Solid;border-top-style: Solid;border-right-style: Solid;border-bottom-style: Solid;border-left-width: 2px;border-right-width: 2px;border-top-width: 2px;border-bottom-width: 2px;border-left-color: #5f5f5f;border-right-color: #5f5f5f;border-top-color: #5f5f5f;border-bottom-color: #5f5f5f;width: 100%;border-spacing: 0px;border-spacing: 0px;" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
            <col style="width: 25.802%;" />
            <col style="width: 74.198%;" />
            <tr valign="top">
                <td colspan="1" rowspan="1" style="width: 25.802%;padding-right: 10px;padding-left: 10px;background-color: #c9c9c9;border-left-width: 3px;border-left-style: Solid;border-left-color: #ffffff;border-right-width: 3px;border-right-style: Solid;border-right-color: #ffffff;border-bottom-width: 3px;border-bottom-color: #ffffff;border-bottom-style: Solid;border-top-width: 3px;border-top-style: Solid;border-top-color: #ffffff;" bgcolor="#C9C9C9" width="25.802%">
                    <p style="font-weight: bold;">guardianPRO disabled for days</p>
                </td>
                <td colspan="1" rowspan="1" style="width: 74.198%;padding-right: 10px;padding-left: 10px;background-color: #eaeaea;border-right-width: 3px;border-right-style: Solid;border-right-color: #ffffff;border-bottom-width: 3px;border-bottom-color: #ffffff;border-bottom-style: Solid;border-top-width: 3px;border-top-color: #ffffff;border-top-style: Solid;" bgcolor="#EAEAEA" width="74.198%">
                    <p>Indicate the days it should be off.</p>
                </td>
            </tr>
            <tr valign="top">
                <td colspan="1" rowspan="1" style="width: 25.802%;padding-right: 10px;padding-left: 10px;background-color: #c9c9c9;border-left-color: #ffffff;border-left-style: Solid;border-left-width: 3px;border-right-color: #ffffff;border-right-style: Solid;border-right-width: 3px;border-bottom-style: Solid;border-bottom-color: #ffffff;border-bottom-width: 3px;" bgcolor="#C9C9C9" width="25.802%">
                    <p style="font-weight: bold;">Enable control on active alarms.</p>
                </td>
                <td colspan="1" rowspan="1" style="width: 74.198%;padding-right: 10px;padding-left: 10px;background-color: #eaeaea;border-right-color: #ffffff;border-right-style: Solid;border-right-width: 3px;border-bottom-style: Solid;border-bottom-color: #ffffff;border-bottom-width: 3px;" bgcolor="#EAEAEA" width="74.198%">
                    <p>Indicates when any alarms are not managed by PlantVisorPRO Locale within a set time band.</p>
                </td>
            </tr>
        </table>
